    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/french-style-mustard-and-garlic-chicken-with-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced chicken thigh </strong>with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until starting to brown</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/french-style-mustard-and-garlic-chicken-with-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> and<strong> cornflour </strong>in 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[170ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>, with your <strong>wholegrain mustard </strong>(not a mustard fan? Go easy!) and <strong>clotted cream</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy stock</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> then add to a colander and pour <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the <strong>wilted</strong> <strong>spinach</strong> under <strong>cold</strong> <strong>running</strong> <strong>water</strong> until it's cool</p><p>Once cool, squeeze as much water out of the spinach as you can</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/french-style-mustard-and-garlic-chicken-with-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Drain and rinse your <strong>green lentils</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/french-style-mustard-and-garlic-chicken-with-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken has browned, add your <strong>dried</strong> <strong>thyme </strong>(not a fan of thyme? Just add a little!) and <strong>roasted</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> <strong>paste</strong> to the pan and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>creamy stock</strong> to the pan<strong> </strong>and bring to the boil</p><p>Season with a very generous grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until thickened</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/french-style-mustard-and-garlic-chicken-with-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Squeeze your pouch[es]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>of <strong>cooked white long grain rice</strong> to separate the grains</p><p>Tear the top corner of the pouch[es]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>(just a little!) and <strong>microwave</strong> for 2 min or until piping hot</p><p>Tip: If you're cooking two pouches, pop them in together but increase the microwave cook time accordingly</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/french-style-mustard-and-garlic-chicken-with-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the sauce has thickened, add the<strong> drained lentils</strong> and <strong>spinach</strong> to the pan</p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for a further 3 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>French-style mustard & garlic chicken</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/french-style-mustard-and-garlic-chicken-with-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>French-style mustard & garlic chicken</strong> over the<strong> cooked rice</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
